Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put the @unsalted butter{10%g} into a #small bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and add the @honey{15%g}. Mash with a fork until softened and combined. Snip the string holding the @whole British chicken{1} legs together and discard it. Transfer the chicken to a #large baking tray{} and cover with the honey butter.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Prick the @sweet potatoes{2} with a fork. Pop them onto the same baking tray, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt.

Roast the chicken and sweet potatoes on the middle shelf of your oven for ~{60-75%minutes} depending on size.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when the juices from the thigh run clear and there is no pink meat.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @dried cranberries{30%g} then add into a #medium bowl{} with the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%g}. Mix to combine, then shape into 3 balls per person. Add to the baking tray when the chicken has ~{30%minutes} remaining.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

> The stuffing balls are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, bring a #medium saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Peel and chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks. Trim the @green beans{150%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add the butter, half the @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt and @pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

Meanwhile, put the @water for the gravy{150%ml} into a #small saucepan{} and add the @red wine jus paste{22%g}. Bring to the boil and simmer until the gravy has thickened to your liking, ~{5-10%minutes}. Then remove from the heat.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @flaked almonds{15%g} and dry-fry, stirring regularly, until lightly toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Once toasted, transfer to a small bowl. Put your pan back on medium-high heat and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}. Then add a splash of water and immediately cover with a lid or some #foil{}. Allow to cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat.

Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a #board{} to rest, loosely wrapped in foil, ~{5-10%minutes}. Cut open the sweet potatoes and add some @?butter{} and the remaining cheese. Reheat anything if needed.

Carve your roast chicken and serve with the mash, sweet potatoes, nutty green beans and stuffing alongside. Finish with the gravy drizzled over the top. Enjoy!